   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_6931_unknown_04_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1111-01-01">Saturday morning</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrinE1">Mrs Brinkley</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
               I cannot let your<lb/>
               excellent <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrinJ1">Doctor</persName> leave us without<lb/>
               expressing to you our regret<lb/>
               that you could not have <choice>
                  <orig>ac-<lb/>
               -companied</orig>
                  <reg>accompanied</reg>
               </choice> him - and that<lb/>
               he leaves us so soon-<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               I am sure you <del>would</del> even<lb/>
               you would accuse me<lb/>
               of exaggeration were I to<lb/>
               tell you in sober truth how<lb/>
               much he has delighted<lb/>
               us all - <unclear>but</unclear> particularly<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeW1">William</persName> - to whom<lb/>
               he is not only the greatest<lb/>
               pleasure but of the greatest<lb/>
               <unclear>use</unclear> -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_6931_unknown_04_page02.jpg"/>
               He will tell you all about<lb/>
               us so that I shall spare<lb/>
               your <unclear>eyes</unclear> and only say<lb/>
               that our poor dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeL1">Lucy</persName>
               <lb/>
               has borne her Sisters <choice>
                  <orig>depar-<lb/>
               ture</orig>
                  <reg>departure</reg>
               </choice> better than could have<lb/>
               been expected - but that<lb/>
               dear little object of our <choice>
                  <orig>affec<lb/>
               tion</orig>
                  <reg>affection</reg>
               </choice>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeS1">Sophy</persName> will soon fly<lb/>
               off to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#ENK">England</placeName> perhaps to<lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#IT">Italy</placeName> - and then poor<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeL1">Lucy</persName> will be tried <choice>
                  <orig>in-<lb/>
               -deed</orig>
                  <reg>indeed</reg>
               </choice> - It is a happy<lb/>
               thing to settle a daughter &amp;<lb/>
               a happy thing to see her<lb/>
               happy - but alas there<lb/>
               is much bitter mingled<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_6931_unknown_04_page03.jpg"/>
               with the sweet - and I<lb/>
               am not quite so sure that<lb/>
               it sets it off as shade does<lb/>
               light - Howbeit it is the<lb/>
               will of God that it should be<lb/>
               so - and we cannot be<lb/>
               sorry when we say &amp; feel<lb/>
               that he knows best<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               Ever your dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrinE1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
                  <lb/>
               Brinkley</persName> &amp; ever your<lb/>
               Affectionate <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">F<unclear>E</unclear>
               </persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
         </div>
